ou try!', 3, 0), (7880, 'The Guide says there is an art to flying", said Ford, "or rather a knack. The knack lies in learning how to throw yourself at the ground and miss.', 386, 0), (7881, 'Basically, I have two speeds.... Hostile or smart-aleck. Your choice.', 285, 0), (7882, 'If writers wrote as carelessly as some people talk, then adhasdh asdglaseuyt[bn[ pasdlgkhasdfasdf.', 59, 0), (7883, 'Right now I’m having amnesia and déjà vu at the same time. I think I’ve forgotten this before.', 922, 0), (7884, 'Mom. I have something to tell you. I’m undead. Now, I know you may have some preconceived notions about the undead. I know you may not be comfortable with the idea of me being undead. But I’m here to tell you that undead are just like you and me … well, okay. Possibly more like me than you.', 39, 0), (7885, 'Just because you call an electric eel a rubber duck doesn''t make it a rubber duck, does it? And God help the poor bastard who decides they want to take a bath with the duckie. (Jace Wayland)', 39, 0), (7886, 'How do you feel, Georgie?" whispered Mrs. Weasley.George''s fingers groped for the side of his head."Saintlike," he murmured."What''s wrong with him?" croaked Fred, looking terrified. "Is his mind affected?""Saintlike," repeated George, opening his eyes and looking up at his brother. "You see...I''m HOLEY, Fred, geddit?', 28, 0), (7887, 'Holey? You have the the whole world of ear-related humor before you, you go for holey?', 28, 0), (7888, 'Now, you two – this year, you behave yourselves. If I get one more owl telling me you''ve – you''ve blown up a toilet or –""Blown up a toilet? We''ve never blown up a toilet.""Great idea though, thanks, Mum.', 28, 0), (7889, 'What would men be without women? Scarce, sir...mighty scarce.', 286, 0), (7890, 'Out of the corner of her eye she thought she saw Jace shoot her a look of white rage - but when she glanced at him, he looked as he always did: easy, confident, slightly bored."In future, Clarissa," he said, "it might be wise to mention that you already have a man in your bed, to avoid such tedious situations."" Simon demanded, looking shaken."Ridiculous, isn''t it?" said Jace. "We would never have all fit.""I didn''t invite him into bed," Clary snapped. "We were just kissing.""Just kissing?" Jace''s tone mocked her with its false hurt. "How swiftly you dismiss our love.', 39, 0), (7891, 'Don''t Panic.', 386, 0), (7892, 'Do your thing and don''t care if they like it.', 1219, 0), (7893, 'Oh well... I''d just been thinking, if you had died, you''d have been welcome to share my toilet.', 28, 0), (7894, 'History will be kind to me for I intend to write it.', 1150, 0), (7895, 'Isabelle drifted over, Jace a pace behind her. She was wearing a long black dress with boots and an even longer cutaway coat of soft green velvet, the color of moss. "I can''t believe you did it!" she exclaimed. "How did you get Magnus to let Jace leave?""Traded him for Alec," Clary said.Isabelle looked mildly alarmed. "Not permanently?""No," said Jace. "Just for a few hours. Unless I don''t come back," he added thoughtfully. "In which case, maybe he does get to keep Alec. Think of it as a lease with an option to buy."Isabelle looked dubious. "Mom and Dad won''t be pleased if they find out.""That you freed a possible criminal by trading away your brother to a warlock who looks like a gay Sonic the Hedgehog and dresses like the Child Catcher from Chitty Chitty Bang Bang?" Simon inquired. "No, probably not.', 39, 0), (7896, 'It is a great thing to start life with a small number of really good books which are your very own.', 764, 0), (7897, 'Say ''provoking'' again. Your mouth looks provocative when you do.', 155, 0), (7898, 'Yeah, Quirrell was a great teacher. There was just that minor drawback of him having Lord Voldemort sticking out of the back of his head!', 28, 0), (7899, 'Finally, from so little sleeping and so much reading, his brain dried up and he went completely out of his mind.', 1318, 0), (7900, 'Fighting for peace is like screwing for virginity.', 1003, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (7901, 'You here to finish me off, Sweetheart?', 18, 0), (7902, 'The meek may inherit the earth, but at the moment it belongs to the conceited. Like me.', 39, 0), (7903, 'When I was a boy of 14, my father was so ignorant I could hardly stand to have the old man around. But when I got to be 21, I was astonished at how much the old man had learned in seven years.', 286, 0), (7904, 'Some people say, “Never let them see you cry.” I say, if you’re so mad you could just cry, then cry. It terrifies everyone.', 1219, 0), (7905, 'I''m not going to wear a red dress," she said."It would look stunning, My Lady," she called.She spoke to the bubbles gathered on the surface of the water. "If there''s anyone I wish to stun at dinner, I''ll hit him in the face.', 371, 0), (7906, 'Have you ever noticed that anybody driving slower than you is an idiot, and anyone going faster than you is a maniac?', 1003, 0), (7907, 'Time is a drug. Too much of it kills you.', 195, 0), (7908, 'Why were you lurking under our window?""Yes - yes, good point, Petunia! What were you doing under our windows, boy?""Listening to the news," said Harry in a resigned voice.His aunt and uncle exchanged looks of outrage."Listening to the news! Again?""Well, it changes every day, you see," said Harry.', 28, 0), (7909, 'What are all these?" Clary asked."Vials of holy water, blessed knives, steel and silver blades," Jace said, piling the weapons on the floor beside him, "electrum wire - not much use at the moment but it''s always good to have spares - silver bullets, charms of protetion, crucifixes, stars of David-""Jesus," said Clary"I doubt he''d fit.""Jace." Clary was appalled.', 39, 0), (7910, 'Of all the trees we could''ve hit, we had to get one that hits back.', 28, 0), (7911, 'Yes, frosting. The final defense of the dying.', 18, 0), (7912, 'The real story of the Fleece: there were these two children of Zeus, Cadmus and Europa, okay? They were about to get offered up as human sacrifices, when they prayed to Zeus to save them. So Zeus sent this magical flying ram with golden wool, which picked them up in Greece and carried them all the way to Colchis in Asia Minor. Well, actually it carried Cadmus. Europa fell off and died along the way, but that''s not important.""It was probably important to her.', 80, 0), (7913, 'Do you wish me a good morning, or mean that it is a good morning whether I want it or not; or that you feel good this morning; or that it is a morning to be good on?', 65, 0), (7914, 'Sometimes when I''m talking, my words can''t keep up with my thoughts. I wonder why we think faster than we speak. Probably so we can think twice.', 983, 0), (7915, 'You possess other people''s...bodies."He accepted that statement with a nod."Do you want to possess my body?""I want to do a lot of things to your body, but that''s not one of them.', 155, 0), (7916, 'He was my mum and dad''s best friend. He''s a convicted murderer, but he''s broken out of wizard prison and he''s on the run. He likes to keep in touch with me, though...keep up with my news...check if I''m happy...', 28, 0), (7917, 'So when the moon''s only partly full, you only feel a little wolfy?" "You could say that.""Well, you can go ahead and hang your head out the car window if you feel like it.""I''m a werewolf, not a golden retriever.', 39, 0), (7918, 'From the moment I picked up your book until I put it down, I was convulsed with laughter. Some day I intend reading it.', 1040, 0), (7919, 'Every now and then I like to do as I''m told, just to confuse people.', 2177, 0), (7920, 'The capacity for friendship is God''s way of apologizing for our families.', 2178, 0), (7921, 'Today was good. Today was fun. Tomorrow is another one.', 3, 0), (7922, 'I''m tough, I''m ambitious, and I know exactly what I want. If that makes me a bitch, okay.', 373, 0), (7923, 'That''s why they call it the American Dream, because you have to be asleep to believe it.', 1003, 0), (7924, 'Your friend''s poetry is terrible," he said.Clary blinked, caught momentarily off guard. "What?""I said his poetry was terrible. It sounds like he ate a dictionary and started vomiting up words at random.', 39, 0), (7925, 'If you ever find yourself in the wrong story, leave.', 2179, 0), (7926, 'I''ll just have them change the entry in the demonology textbook from ''almost extinct'' to ''not extinct enough for Alec. He prefers his monsters really, really extinct.'' Will that make you happy?', 39, 0), (7927, 'Don''t feel bad, I''m usually about to die.', 80, 0), (7928, 'Beauty is only skin deep, but ugly goes clean to the bone.', 201, 0), (7929, 'In a way, it''s nice to know that there are Greek gods out there, because you have somebody to blame when things go wrong. For instance, when you''re walking away from a bus that''s just been attacked by monster hags and blown up by lightning, and it''s raining on top of everything else, most people might think that''s just really bad luck; when you''re a half-blood, you understand that some devine force is really trying to mess up your day.', 80, 0), (7930, 'It is forbidden to kill', 2180, 0), (7931, 'From there to here, from here to there, funny things are everywhere!', 3, 0), (7932, 'It''s not gray," Clary felt compelled to point out. "It''s green.""If there was such a thing as terminal literalism, you''d have died in childhood," said Jace.', 39, 0), (7933, 'Would it save you a lot of time if I just gave up and went mad now?', 386, 0), (7934, 'Beautiful face. Beautiful body. Horrible attitude. It was the holy trinity of hot boys.', 366, 0), (7935, 'Because you can''t argue with all the fools in the world. It''s easier to let them have their way, then trick them when they''re not paying attention.', 480, 0), (7936, 'Must you go? I was rather hoping you''d stay and be a ministering angel, but if you must go, you must.""I''ll stay," Will said a bit crossly, and threw himself down in the armchair Tessa had just vacated. 